<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Page Navigation</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/assets/styles.css">
</head>

<body>
<div id="articlestop">
  <%= image_tag "goldenrodcity.jpg", class: "article-imagetop" %>
</div>

<div id="articles">

    <div class="tracker">
        <div class="navbar">
            <a href="index">Home</a>
            <a href="#">Pokédex</a>
            <a href="tracker">Pokémon Tracker</a>
            <a href="staff">Our Staff</a>
            <a href="about">About</a>
        </div>
        <h2>Pokémon Tracker</h2>
        <p>The Pokémon Tracker for speedrunners is a user-friendly web page designed to assist players in tracking their progress in capturing Pokemon during speedruns. It features a grid layout displaying all Pokemon sprites, allowing players to easily visualize their collection. The interface allows players to mark a Pokemon as caught by left-clicking on its sprite. Conversely, right-clicking a Pokemon sprite marks it as a target to be caught. This intuitive design streamlines the tracking process, enabling speedrunners to efficiently manage their progress and optimize their gameplay strategies.</p>
        <h2>INSTRUCTIONS:</h2>
         <br>
        <p><b>Step 1:</b> Click the Pokémon you want to track</p>
        <br>
        <p><b>Step 2:</b> Left click to remove a Pokémon from the box</p>
        <br>
        <p><b>Step 3:</b> Right click once to mark a Pokémon as planned</p>
        <br>
        <p><b>Step 4:</b> Right click twice to mark a Pokémon as caught</p>
        <br>
        <p><b>Step 5:</b> Right click thrice to unmark a Pokémon</p>
        <br>
         <div id="color-selector">
          <label for="background-color"><b>Step 7</b>: Click to pick a color:</label>
          <input type="color" id="background-color">
        </div>

        <div class="boxtop">
            <div id="counter-container">
                <span id="blue-counter"><b>0</b></span> Pokémon planned and
                <span id="pink-counter"><b>0</b></span> Pokémon caught
            </div>
        </div>


        <div class="pokebox"></div>

        <h2>Red & Blue - Generation 1</h2>
        <%= render partial: 'shared/pokemon_sprites_normal' %>
        <h2>Red & Blue - Shiny Generation 1</h2>
        <%= render partial: 'shared/pokemon_sprites_shiny' %>
        <h2>Gold & Silver - Generation 2</h2>
        <%= render partial: 'shared/pokemon_sprites_normal2' %>
        <h2>Gold & Silver - Shiny Generation 2</h2>
        <%= render partial: 'shared/pokemon_sprites_shiny2' %>
        <h2>Ruby & Sapphire - Generation 3</h2>
        <%= render partial: 'shared/pokemon_sprites_normal_rs' %>
        <h2>Ruby & Sapphire - Shiny Generation 3</h2>
        <%= render partial: 'shared/pokemon_sprites_shiny_rs' %>

        <button class="donate-button">Donate</button>
    </div>

</div>
<script>


  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
    const pokebox = document.querySelector(".pokebox");
    const colorSelector = document.getElementById("background-color");

    colorSelector.addEventListener("change", function() {
      const selectedColor = colorSelector.value;
      pokebox.style.backgroundColor = selectedColor;
    });
  });
</script>
</body>
</html>
